 Steve Smith , 52 , grew up helping his father run a stall at Bilston market in the West Midlands , opened his first Poundland shop in Burton-upon-Trent at the age of 18 in 1990 .
The venture was an overnight success and he became a self-made millionaire when he sold the company for a staggering £ 50million 10 years later .
Mr Smith gave half of his profits - £ 25million to his parents .